cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.DL, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the co-evolutionary dynamics of online social networks, specifically Twitter. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a method to infer new retweet-driven follower relations, which involves software development and implementation. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another possible category as the paper discusses the implications of co-evolutionary dynamics on the topology and function of a social network. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a possible category as the paper involves tracking and analyzing large amounts of data from Twitter users. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a probabilistic model to predict the formation of new retweet-driven follower relations.
